<h2 id="what-is-tigertango">What is TigerTango?</h2>

<p>Playing music requires a <strong>software interface</strong>. Programs like Spotify or iTunes work for everyday listening, but they lack features tango DJs need: prelistening, stable audio output, and safety features to prevent accidental track changes.</p>

<p>Professional DJ tools like Virtual DJ, Traktor, and Serato meet some of these needs, but they come with their own problems for tango DJs:</p>
<ul>
  <li>They include many features not used for tango (deck scratching, beat matching)</li>
  <li>Can be difficult to configure appropriately</li>
  <li>Often cost money</li>
</ul>

<p><a href="https://github.com/sericson0/TigerTango">TigerTango</a> is a customized Virtual DJ skin specifically designed for tango DJs. It provides:</p>
<ul>
  <li>The full power and reliability of dedicated DJ software</li>
  <li>A clean interface with unused features removed</li>
  <li>Configuration set up specifically for tango DJing</li>
  <li>Safety features so you can focus on the dancers, not the software</li>
  <li>Built-in semiparametric equalizer</li>
  <li>VST3 plugin integration</li>
  <li>Cortina fade-out buttons</li>
  <li>Optional video skin for displaying song information and lyrics</li>
  <li><strong>Free for all to use</strong></li>
</ul>

