<h2 id="troubleshooting">Troubleshooting</h2>

<div class="faq-list">
  <details>
    <summary><strong>No sound is coming from a deck</strong></summary>
    <p>Check that the deck volume fader is up. TigerTango adjusts deck volume during fading and prelistening, and resets to 100% afterward. If it didn&rsquo;t reset, manually slide it up.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary><strong>I hear a watermark / periodic audio artifact</strong></summary>
    <p>You may have accidentally updated to Virtual DJ 2026. Reinstall the 2025 version from the download buttons above and disable <code>checkUpdates</code> in Options.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary><strong>Pre-listening doesn&rsquo;t work</strong></summary>
    <p>Make sure your audio is configured for Speaker + Headphones (not Speaker only). Also check that the headphone volume in the Master section is turned up and the headphone output is set to a different device than the speakers.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary><strong>Automix is playing from the wrong position</strong></summary>
    <p>When starting or restarting automix, Virtual DJ uses the first instance of a track to determine list position. If you have duplicate tracks (e.g. reusing the same cortina), double-check that automix is playing from where you want.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary><strong>I can&rsquo;t drag tracks onto a deck</strong></summary>
    <p>In automix mode, TigerTango deactivates deck loading as a safety feature (shown by a &oslash; symbol). Right-click the &ldquo;Single Deck / Dual Deck&rdquo; button in the shortcuts area to disable this safety.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary><strong>Warning lights are showing</strong></summary>
    <p>Hover over a warning light to see the issue. Click it to change the setting to the recommended value. Resolve all warnings before starting your set.</p>
  </details>
  <details>
    <summary><strong>CPU usage is high</strong></summary>
    <p>Close other programs or reduce the number of active plugins. Check the CPU indicator in the Info section.</p>
  </details>
</div>

